    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning all yellow and kind of pale. any idea what happened or how to fix it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on the bottom of your tomato plants, especially when they are pale, often point to a few common issues, like a nutrient deficiency or overwatering. It's a classic sign of the plant struggling to pull resources from the lower leaves first. You could try checking your soil moisture—if it's soggy, let it dry out a bit; if it's bone dry, give it a deep drink. Also, consider a balanced fertilizer application, perhaps one higher in nitrogen, to give your plants the boost they need.",
