    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok that makes sense. it just feels like even when i give them fertilizer, it's like the nutrients just vanish before the plants can really use them. is there anything else that could be \"stealing\" the nitrogen or messing with the uptake?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like you might have a root issue, which is a common culprit when nutrients seem to vanish, even when you're feeding them. Poor root health, perhaps from compaction or root rot, can prevent the plant from absorbing anything, no matter how much fertilizer you apply. You could gently check the roots—if they look mushy or black, you might have a rot problem, and you'll need to prune those back and improve drainage. Another possibility is a fungal issue, which can also impede nutrient uptake, so keep a close eye out for any signs of mold or mildew.",
      "source": "target",
